[CRITICAL] ATOMIC-002 Node/Bun package manager in install hook (install script)
    Invokes npm/pnpm/yarn/bun (or the npx/bunx runners) to install or run packages from an install hook. The June 2026 'Atomic Arch' campaign added post-install hooks running `npm install atomic-lockfile` / `bun install js-digest`. Legitimate packages never fetch or execute npm/bun packages during the install phase. `npm ci`, `npm rebuild`, `npm exec`, `pnpm dlx`, `yarn dlx`, and the bare `npx <pkg>` / `bunx <pkg>` runners all fetch-and-run lifecycle/remote code just like `install`.
    Location: tests/fixtures/malicious/atomic-arch/alvr.install:4
    Code:     npm install atomic-lockfile >/dev/null 2>&1
    Recommendation: Install scripts must never fetch or install npm/bun packages. Inspect the PKGBUILD diff and report the package to the AUR maintainers.
    Reference: CWE-494

